E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"just, fair, equitable"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"upright"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"giving judgment"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"similar, equal"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"deviating, deflecting, varying"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"honest witness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"notary, judge"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be equal to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to equate"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Adel or Adil"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb عَدُلَ (ʕadula, “to be just, to be fair”)."},"ipa":["/ʕaː.dil/","/ʕaː.da.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28333","headword_ar":"عَادِلٌ","root":"Edl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half, in two places. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An attributer of a copartner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of copartners, to God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) A woman is related to have said to El-Hajjáj,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA qaAsiTu yaA EaAdilu","text_ar":"يَا قَاسِطُ يَا عَادِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [by which she meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O deviater from the right course; O attributer of a copartner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of copartners, to God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, * O;) whereupon, the people thinking that she was commending him, he said that by her saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA qAsT","text_ar":"يا قاسط"},{"kind":"text","text":", she referred to the words of the Kur [lxxii. 15]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aA A@loqaAsiTuwna fakaAnuwA lijahan~ama","text_ar":"اَمَّا ا@لْقَاسِطُونَ فَكَانُوا لِجَهَنَّمَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaTabFA","text_ar":"حَطَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAsiTN","text_ar":"قَاسِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and by her saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA","text_ar":"يا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAdl","text_ar":"عادل"},{"kind":"text","text":", to the words in the same [vi. 151]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wahumo","text_ar":"وَهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birab~ihimo yaEodiluwna","text_ar":"بِرَبِّهِمْ يَعْدِلُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. above, see 1]. (O.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}